# Contributor Code of Conduct

## Purpose

SkillUp is dedicated to fostering an open and inclusive community where contributors feel welcome and valued. As a contributor, we expect everyone to adhere to this Code of Conduct to create a positive and collaborative environment.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to creating a positive environment include:

- **Respect:** Treat others with respect and kindness, acknowledging different perspectives and experiences.
- **Inclusivity:** Embrace diversity and inclusion. Be mindful of your language and actions to make everyone feel welcome.
- **Collaboration:** Work together with a spirit of cooperation and openness. Encourage participation from all contributors.

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- **Harassment:** Any form of harassment, discrimination, or offensive comments will not be tolerated.
- **Disruptive Behavior:** Avoid disruptive or disrespectful behavior. Be mindful of others' time and efforts.
- **Violation of Privacy:** Respect others' privacy and avoid sharing personal information without consent.

## Responsibilities

Contributors are responsible for:

- Upholding the standards outlined in this Code of Conduct.
- Reporting any behavior inconsistent with this Code of Conduct to project maintainers.
- Maintaining a positive and constructive atmosphere for collaboration.

## Enforcement

Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project maintainers responsible for enforcement. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

Project maintainers have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject comments, commits, code, issues, and other contributions that violate this Code of Conduct. Contributors who do not follow the Code of Conduct may face temporary or permanent actions as determined by the project maintainers.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org), version 2.1, available at [https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct.html](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct.html).

Thank you for your contribution to SkillUp!

